    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** - May 4, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🔐 OpenAI put ChatGPT accounts behind harder locks\n\nThe AI assistant is now important enough to deserve the boring part of banking security. Progress, allegedly.\n\n- **The feature:** OpenAI rolled out Advanced Account Security for high-risk ChatGPT and Codex users on May 4.\n- **The lock:** enabling it disables password login and requires passkeys or physical security keys.\n- **The privacy bit:** enrolled users also get automatic training exclusion, plus tighter recovery and shorter sessions.\n\n*When your chatbot account can touch work, code and secrets, SMS codes start looking very 2014.*\n\n**Sources:** [SecurityWeek](https://www.securityweek.com/openai-rolls-out-advanced-security-for-chatgpt-accounts/) | [Yubico](https://investors.yubico.com/en/openai-and-yubico-partner-to-bring-custom-phishing-resistant-yubikeys-to-openai-users/)\n\n---\n\n## 🛡️ Claude Security moved from demo energy to enterprise beta\n\nThe model race has reached the natural next phase: the AI now reviews the code that the AI helped write.\n\n- **The beta:** Claude Security entered public beta for Claude Enterprise customers, with Team and Max access expected later.\n- **The engine:** Opus 4.7 scans repositories, traces data flows and suggests targeted patches for human review.\n- **The ecosystem:** CrowdStrike and SentinelOne are also folding Opus 4.7 into vulnerability discovery and remediation services.\n\n*Security teams asked for fewer dashboards. They got a frontier model with a findings queue.*\n\n**Sources:** [Help Net Security](https://www.helpnetsecurity.com/2026/05/04/anthropic-claude-security-public-beta/) | [CrowdStrike](https://www.crowdstrike.com/en-us/press-releases/crowdstrike-puts-claude-opus-4-7-to-work-across-falcon-platform-project-quiltworks/) | [SentinelOne](https://www.sentinelone.com/press/sentinelone-unveils-wayfinder-ai/)\n\n---\n\n## 🧩 MediaTek hired a CoWoS veteran because AI chips need more than vibes\n\nEveryone wants AI silicon. The real choke point is still the exquisite sandwich holding the silicon together.\n\n- **The hire:** MediaTek appointed former TSMC executive Douglas Yu as a part-time adviser, Reuters reported on May 4.\n- **The resume:** Yu joined TSMC in 1994 and helped develop advanced packaging, including CoWoS.\n- **The market:** MediaTek said last week it expects multiple billions of dollars in AI accelerator ASIC revenue by 2027.\n\n*The GPU boom has a quiet backend department, and now everyone is trying to poach its memory.*\n\n**Sources:** [Reuters via MarketScreener](https://www.marketscreener.com/news/moves-mediatek-hires-former-tsmc-executive-to-boost-ai-chip-packaging-ce7f58deda8afe24)\n\n---\n\n## 🤖 Linkerbot wants a $6B hand, because humanoids still need fingers\n\nThe humanoid race keeps showing faces and walking demos. The money is staring at the wrists.\n\n- **The target:** Reuters reported that Beijing-based Linkerbot will seek a $6 billion valuation in its next financing round.\n- **The jump:** the company just closed a Series B+ round at a $3 billion valuation.\n- **The claim:** CEO Alex Zhou says Linkerbot has more than 80% of the high-DoF robotic hand market and is scaling toward 10,000 units a month.\n\n*Apparently the future of labor automation starts with making sure the robot can actually pick up the tool.*\n\n**Sources:** [Reuters via Investing.com](https://www.investing.com/news/stock-market-news/exclusivechina-robothandbuilding-unicorn-linkerbot-targets-6-billion-valuation-4654932)\n"
  }
]
